1
00:00:00,000 --> 00:00:07,000
( Watch on www.kissasia.co, .be, .org, .net, .id, .xyz )

2
00:00:09,220 --> 00:00:12,050
Phoon, do you want to move in with me?

3
00:00:13,000 --> 00:00:14,973
You won’t get bored of me, right, P'Fah?

4
00:00:15,071 --> 00:00:16,011
No way.

5
00:00:16,084 --> 00:00:18,250
Do you want to see your mom?

6
00:00:18,737 --> 00:00:20,988
You said you’d take me anywhere I want to go.

7
00:00:21,620 --> 00:00:23,114
I already know where I want to go.

8
00:00:23,688 --> 00:00:25,591
P'Fah, can we head back now?

9
00:00:26,010 --> 00:00:28,968
- Why?
- I didn’t think it would be this cold.

10
00:00:29,306 --> 00:00:30,720
Help me find Phoon's mom.

11
00:00:31,589 --> 00:00:32,487
His real mom.

12
00:00:32,717 --> 00:00:34,712
Could you stop interfering with Phoon's life?

13
00:00:34,951 --> 00:00:36,654
He has endured enough already.

14
00:00:36,902 --> 00:00:38,294
Please let him go.

15
00:00:42,714 --> 00:00:45,053
Thank you, P'Fah, for helping me find my mom.

16
00:00:48,567 --> 00:00:49,677
It’s nothing.

17
00:00:56,090 --> 00:00:57,802
Half Japanese.

18
00:00:59,253 --> 00:01:03,522
She has one son and is now 39 years old.

19
00:01:04,922 --> 00:01:08,837
Then she must have had me at 19.

20
00:01:12,691 --> 00:01:13,774
P'Fah.

21
00:01:14,808 --> 00:01:15,417
Yes?

22
00:01:15,798 --> 00:01:17,789
She must not have been ready when she had me.

23
00:01:21,494 --> 00:01:23,162
Ready or not, I don’t know.

24
00:01:23,829 --> 00:01:26,554
But she sent you gifts every year, didn’t she?

25
00:01:28,045 --> 00:01:29,312
Besides,

26
00:01:30,262 --> 00:01:32,383
Your name and your mom’s in Japanese,

27
00:01:33,728 --> 00:01:35,592
they both mean flowers.

28
00:01:37,127 --> 00:01:38,351
How so?

29
00:01:39,888 --> 00:01:40,865
Yuri.

30
00:01:41,241 --> 00:01:42,481
It means lily.

31
00:01:43,115 --> 00:01:44,739
And Ren means lotus.

32
00:01:52,717 --> 00:01:54,336
Do you want to see your mom?

33
00:01:57,345 --> 00:01:58,342
I’m not sure.

34
00:01:59,480 --> 00:02:01,154
She already has a new family.

35
00:02:01,678 --> 00:02:03,417
If I go see her, I’m afraid

36
00:02:04,400 --> 00:02:07,368
I might ruin the new life she’s built.

37
00:02:09,699 --> 00:02:12,994
Then why don’t you try contacting her first?

38
00:02:14,072 --> 00:02:17,222
If she seems uncomfortable, you can step back.

39
00:02:21,247 --> 00:02:23,305
Did I make you feel uneasy?

40
00:02:24,589 --> 00:02:25,835
You don’t have to overthink it.

41
00:02:26,970 --> 00:02:28,373
If you don’t want to go, it’s okay.

42
00:02:31,979 --> 00:02:33,194
Actually,

43
00:02:34,371 --> 00:02:35,979
I do want to see her at least once.

44
00:02:47,457 --> 00:02:48,917
Her son’s name is Daiki.

45
00:02:50,143 --> 00:02:51,460
I’m going to have a younger sibling.

46
00:02:52,557 --> 00:02:53,585
That’s cute.

47
00:04:32,598 --> 00:04:34,242
Maew, are you mixed?

48
00:04:35,623 --> 00:04:36,680
Not exactly.

49
00:04:38,536 --> 00:04:40,614
My mom is mixed.

50
00:04:41,610 --> 00:04:44,841
Oh, so you’re 25% Japanese?

51
00:04:46,788 --> 00:04:49,630
You get half from your mom, right?

52
00:04:51,499 --> 00:04:52,376
So?

53
00:04:53,022 --> 00:04:54,397
Are you going to see her?

54
00:04:56,155 --> 00:04:57,241
I don’t know.

55
00:04:57,795 --> 00:04:59,245
My mom already has a new family.

56
00:05:00,051 --> 00:05:01,460
I don’t know

57
00:05:02,143 --> 00:05:03,700
if I should go or not.

58
00:05:06,994 --> 00:05:08,167
I think you should.

59
00:05:08,955 --> 00:05:10,611
She probably misses you a lot.

60
00:05:11,161 --> 00:05:13,223
Otherwise, why would she send gifts?

61
00:05:13,367 --> 00:05:14,442
Yeah, true.

62
00:05:16,146 --> 00:05:17,477
Why don’t you try contacting her first?

63
00:05:18,771 --> 00:05:19,922
Like sending a letter.

64
00:05:24,549 --> 00:05:25,031
Well,

65
00:05:25,777 --> 00:05:26,660
that could work.

66
00:05:27,320 --> 00:05:28,632
I’ll write her a letter first.

67
00:05:28,811 --> 00:05:30,484
If she doesn’t reply, I’ll deal with it then.

68
00:05:31,352 --> 00:05:32,933
She will reply.

69
00:05:35,171 --> 00:05:36,527
Anyway, congratulations.

70
00:05:37,053 --> 00:05:40,465
You finally know who your mom is.

71
00:05:41,257 --> 00:05:41,826
Yeah.

72
00:05:45,400 --> 00:05:46,764
What about your dad?

73
00:05:51,902 --> 00:05:53,355
That’s probably over now.

74
00:05:54,074 --> 00:05:55,792
He’s already paid for what he did.

75
00:05:56,573 --> 00:05:58,118
I’ll live my own life.

76
00:05:58,844 --> 00:06:00,927
Living separately like this is fine.

77
00:06:06,721 --> 00:06:08,262
I’m really proud of you.

78
00:06:08,949 --> 00:06:12,617
You’ve grown so much. You’ve really matured.

79
00:06:12,948 --> 00:06:16,274
- You used to cry whenever your dad came up.
- True.

80
00:06:16,663 --> 00:06:20,585
- You did great.
- Whenever he talked about his dad, his face was like a cat that ate poop.

81
00:06:23,816 --> 00:06:25,108
What’s wrong with you?

82
00:06:27,814 --> 00:06:28,951
Serves you right.

83
00:06:29,327 --> 00:06:30,327
There you go again.

84
00:06:30,733 --> 00:06:31,617
Thanks.

85
00:06:33,088 --> 00:06:34,721
When I was at my worst,

86
00:06:34,885 --> 00:06:35,939
you guys were the only ones

87
00:06:36,426 --> 00:06:37,448
who made things better.

88
00:06:40,905 --> 00:06:42,395
I’m an unlucky guy.

89
00:06:43,000 --> 00:06:45,038
I used up all my luck

90
00:06:45,447 --> 00:06:47,299
on meeting good friends like you guys.

91
00:06:51,949 --> 00:06:56,005
- Maew, stop it, he’s about to cry.
- I’m not crying. You are. Don’t push it.

92
00:06:56,315 --> 00:06:58,314
You’re sniffling.

93
00:06:58,994 --> 00:07:01,442
Maew, honestly, it’s nothing.

94
00:07:01,783 --> 00:07:03,414
You don’t have to thank us.

95
00:07:04,437 --> 00:07:05,896
Just pay for our drinks instead.

96
00:07:09,321 --> 00:07:11,022
Seriously.

97
00:07:11,324 --> 00:07:14,928
You have zero common sense and can’t read the room.

98
00:07:17,065 --> 00:07:19,025
I just don’t like this kind of mood.

99
00:07:19,225 --> 00:07:20,379
It’s too tense.

100
00:07:25,515 --> 00:07:26,727
Hey.

101
00:07:29,954 --> 00:07:30,866
Thanks.

102
00:07:32,811 --> 00:07:33,554
What are you saying?

103
00:07:35,675 --> 00:07:38,257
Thanks for helping me with everything.

104
00:07:38,648 --> 00:07:40,401
And when Phoon got into trouble, too.

105
00:07:41,222 --> 00:07:42,194
Do you even realize?

106
00:07:42,480 --> 00:07:45,980
- You’re like the group’s hero.
- Hero, my ass.

107
00:07:46,629 --> 00:07:50,390
- Are you crazy, thanking me out of nowhere?
- North’s blushing.

108
00:07:50,837 --> 00:07:52,143
I’m serious.

109
00:07:53,216 --> 00:07:55,080
I’m really glad to have a friend like you.

110
00:07:55,580 --> 00:07:57,549
Having a friend like you in this life

111
00:08:00,096 --> 00:08:01,656
is better than winning the lottery.

112
00:08:05,247 --> 00:08:06,225
I really love you.

113
00:08:07,268 --> 00:08:09,555
Hey, what kind of love talk is that?

114
00:08:10,290 --> 00:08:12,712
Are you crazy, Ter? What are you saying?

115
00:08:12,771 --> 00:08:15,524
- No way.
- Acting cool, but you’re blushed, right?

116
00:08:16,097 --> 00:08:18,851
- No, I’m not.
- You are blushed.

117
00:08:18,902 --> 00:08:20,733
- I can tell.
- Are you nuts? Enough.

118
00:08:20,783 --> 00:08:24,349
There are tons of people here. What are you doing?

119
00:08:25,696 --> 00:08:26,930
But really,

120
00:08:29,330 --> 00:08:30,349
I’m really happy

121
00:08:30,681 --> 00:08:31,722
to have you as my friend.

122
00:08:34,160 --> 00:08:37,641
Do you know you’ve always been positive energy for us?

123
00:08:42,677 --> 00:08:43,591
Love you, man.

124
00:08:44,044 --> 00:08:46,048
Hey, stop with the love stuff. No.

125
00:08:46,070 --> 00:08:49,103
- Say you love us.
- What love nonsense again?

126
00:08:49,130 --> 00:08:52,251
- I was getting emotional just now.
- Emotional about what?

127
00:08:52,487 --> 00:08:55,305
- Hurry up.
- Ter, behave yourself.

128
00:08:55,794 --> 00:08:56,755
Are you crazy?

129
00:08:57,955 --> 00:08:58,703
He's just shy.

130
00:09:02,100 --> 00:09:03,460
Three people are done.

131
00:09:09,897 --> 00:09:12,706
No, I’m not saying it.

132
00:09:12,921 --> 00:09:13,602
Hey.

133
00:09:20,931 --> 00:09:24,063
- Thanks, Dao.
- Thanks so much, Dao.

134
00:09:24,235 --> 00:09:26,256
Dao gives really good advice.

135
00:09:26,337 --> 00:09:29,059
- If we don't have you.
- Seriously, the group would’ve fallen apart.

136
00:09:29,080 --> 00:09:31,435
We’d be screwed without Dao.

137
00:09:31,465 --> 00:09:33,093
I’m really glad.

138
00:09:33,160 --> 00:09:35,087
Even though you never eat with us.

139
00:09:47,310 --> 00:09:50,143
To Ms. Nakamura Yuri.

140
00:09:55,093 --> 00:09:57,324
Hello, my name is Typhoon.

141
00:09:57,410 --> 00:10:01,642
I am your son. May I call you Mom?

142
00:10:02,124 --> 00:10:06,371
I don’t know if it’s okay to write to you.

143
00:10:07,272 --> 00:10:12,722
But I want you to know how happy I am to know who my real mom is.

144
00:10:12,986 --> 00:10:18,102
I only recently found out that someone sent me birthday gifts every year.

145
00:10:19,365 --> 00:10:24,454
If it was you, I’m happy you still think of me.

146
00:10:38,164 --> 00:10:41,349
I’m not angry that you weren’t with me.

147
00:10:42,360 --> 00:10:47,619
No matter the reason, I just hope you’re doing well.

148
00:11:29,060 --> 00:11:30,600
As for me, I’m doing well.

149
00:11:31,315 --> 00:11:34,453
I’ve met someone I love, and who loves me.

150
00:11:37,368 --> 00:11:38,499
Thank you.

151
00:11:38,696 --> 00:11:40,720
Can I hire you to dress me for life?

152
00:11:40,971 --> 00:11:43,518
Sure, but

153
00:11:43,934 --> 00:11:44,985
there’s a small fee.

154
00:11:47,200 --> 00:11:48,634
Is it expensive?

155
00:11:49,546 --> 00:11:51,954
Not at all. Just...

156
00:11:52,983 --> 00:11:53,737
one kiss.

157
00:11:58,678 --> 00:12:00,700
What are you saying?

158
00:12:01,709 --> 00:12:03,168
You’ve gotten really cute lately.

159
00:12:04,512 --> 00:12:07,074
Whenever I talk like that, you get shy.

160
00:12:08,463 --> 00:12:09,585
You’re cute, P'Fah.

161
00:12:11,838 --> 00:12:13,177
Stop it.

162
00:12:17,930 --> 00:12:21,250
I have friends and good people around me.

163
00:12:22,882 --> 00:12:23,761
Hey.

164
00:12:37,266 --> 00:12:38,442
Faculty of Fine Arts.

165
00:12:49,131 --> 00:12:51,930
I’ve found my purpose and goals in life.

166
00:12:52,230 --> 00:12:56,835
If one day you ever wonder whether I’m doing well,

167
00:12:57,284 --> 00:12:59,711
I’m doing fine. Don’t worry.

168
00:13:00,882 --> 00:13:01,896
Do you best, Phoon.

169
00:13:03,262 --> 00:13:03,967
Ok.

170
00:13:19,900 --> 00:13:21,829
I want to see you, Mom.

171
00:13:22,620 --> 00:13:27,084
But if you don’t want to see me, that’s okay. I understand.

172
00:13:27,401 --> 00:13:33,385
I wish you happiness and smiles every day. From Typhoon.

173
00:13:33,866 --> 00:13:34,579
Ren.

174
00:14:14,548 --> 00:14:15,269
Is there any?

175
00:14:16,315 --> 00:14:17,183
Just a moment.

176
00:14:34,680 --> 00:14:37,900
Maybe she doesn’t want to see me.

177
00:14:38,749 --> 00:14:40,225
That’s why she hasn’t replied.

178
00:14:43,857 --> 00:14:45,250
Don’t jump to conclusions.

179
00:14:55,002 --> 00:14:56,774
What are you going to do next?

180
00:14:57,328 --> 00:14:58,985
I will probably look for work.

181
00:14:59,162 --> 00:15:01,530
Start a new life with Fai, just the two of us.

182
00:15:03,377 --> 00:15:04,650
That must be tough.

183
00:15:05,248 --> 00:15:08,494
At least I’ll have peace of mind knowing no one will hurt us again.

184
00:15:09,194 --> 00:15:10,410
You too, Phoon.

185
00:15:10,638 --> 00:15:12,373
Live your life happily.

186
00:15:12,702 --> 00:15:14,986
I’ll bring Fai to visit often.

187
00:15:16,004 --> 00:15:16,551
Okay.

188
00:15:16,945 --> 00:15:18,896
Please take good care of yourself, Aunt Phrae.

189
00:15:41,536 --> 00:15:42,317
You’re back?

190
00:16:24,644 --> 00:16:27,287
Ren, I’m sorry. I miss you. I’ll wait.
From Mom

191
00:16:31,248 --> 00:16:32,328
That’s wonderful.

192
00:16:37,210 --> 00:16:37,761
Yeah.

193
00:16:47,734 --> 00:16:49,554
Enjoy your sweets.

194
00:16:56,551 --> 00:16:58,419
What does it mean?

195
00:17:00,235 --> 00:17:02,687
It means “Enjoy your sweets.”

196
00:17:17,419 --> 00:17:18,518
I will

197
00:17:19,031 --> 00:17:20,367
take you to see your mom.

198
00:17:23,008 --> 00:17:24,242
You're so kind.

199
00:17:24,948 --> 00:17:26,983
Hmm? Me?

200
00:17:28,016 --> 00:17:28,555
Yes.

201
00:17:29,785 --> 00:17:31,653
You must get complimented a lot, huh?

202
00:17:33,677 --> 00:17:34,914
Not really.

203
00:17:35,362 --> 00:17:37,072
With other people, it’s just normal.

204
00:17:37,899 --> 00:17:38,872
But with you…

205
00:17:41,605 --> 00:17:43,680
I can really do anything for you.

206
00:17:49,290 --> 00:17:51,797
I can’t wait to see what the dessert looks like.

207
00:17:53,470 --> 00:17:54,266
How to open it?

208
00:17:55,333 --> 00:17:56,019
Here you go.

209
00:18:05,706 --> 00:18:08,050
This is called Manju.

210
00:18:15,001 --> 00:18:16,228
Do you want to try it, P'Fah?

211
00:18:16,709 --> 00:18:17,672
You try it first, Phoon.

212
00:18:30,391 --> 00:18:31,522
Here.

213
00:18:31,591 --> 00:18:32,696
My mom sent it for me.

214
00:18:34,210 --> 00:18:37,765
Wow, you’re all smiles just thinking about seeing your mama.

215
00:18:38,619 --> 00:18:40,008
Let him smile for once.

216
00:18:40,539 --> 00:18:42,924
- True.
- Sure.

217
00:18:43,031 --> 00:18:44,355
Congrats, Maew.

218
00:18:44,595 --> 00:18:45,256
Mm.

219
00:18:45,960 --> 00:18:47,631
So where are you meeting your mama?

220
00:18:49,022 --> 00:18:51,896
She sent me the address. We’ll meet there.

221
00:18:52,085 --> 00:18:54,291
There? Japan?

222
00:18:54,589 --> 00:18:55,162
Yeah.

223
00:18:55,717 --> 00:18:57,269
Whoa.

224
00:18:57,620 --> 00:19:01,635
So that means you and P'Fah get to go on another date in Japan, right?

225
00:19:01,730 --> 00:19:03,663
- Hey!
- No, no!

226
00:19:03,783 --> 00:19:07,028
Hey, Ter, stop teasing him. Look at that smile—his cheeks must hurt already.

227
00:19:07,779 --> 00:19:09,826
Awww, so much shy, huh.

228
00:19:12,100 --> 00:19:14,322
I'm just happy. What’s wrong with that?

229
00:19:16,591 --> 00:19:18,949
- Here, take some sweets.
- Thanks.

230
00:19:18,955 --> 00:19:20,503
Handing out snacks!

231
00:19:20,527 --> 00:19:21,949
- I’ll give you two.
- Thanks a lot.

232
00:19:22,300 --> 00:19:25,348
- Here.
- Hey, why do I only get one? Can I have two?

233
00:19:25,355 --> 00:19:27,242
- He eats a lot.
- Why?.

234
00:19:27,324 --> 00:19:30,570
- You're not handsome enough to get two.
- Then it should be you who get just one.

235
00:19:31,103 --> 00:19:32,094
- Hey!
- Too slow.

236
00:19:32,825 --> 00:19:34,118
Speed belongs to the devil—don’t compete with me.

237
00:19:34,197 --> 00:19:35,663
You steal my stuff all the time.

238
00:19:36,648 --> 00:19:37,954
You didn’t even split the bill last time.

239
00:19:38,528 --> 00:19:39,662
Look at you, pretending to be sulky.

240
00:19:44,850 --> 00:19:47,485
- Here, kids.
- Thank you.

241
00:19:47,823 --> 00:19:49,200
Thank you.

242
00:19:54,173 --> 00:19:55,032
Oh, P'Gib.

243
00:19:57,758 --> 00:19:58,860
My mom sent these.

244
00:19:59,287 --> 00:20:01,302
Whoa.

245
00:20:03,417 --> 00:20:04,853
- Wow.
- Would you like to try some?

246
00:20:05,617 --> 00:20:07,115
Thank you, Phoon.

247
00:20:08,020 --> 00:20:12,773
Ever since you started dating Doctor Fah, you’re glowing.

248
00:20:14,383 --> 00:20:16,030
That’s what love does.

249
00:20:16,320 --> 00:20:17,260
Not just that.

250
00:20:17,472 --> 00:20:20,710
- He's even going on a honeymoon in Japan.
- What honeymoon?

251
00:20:20,740 --> 00:20:22,037
You’re exaggerating, North.

252
00:20:22,051 --> 00:20:23,878
Don’t tell me you’ve already packed your bags.

253
00:20:24,001 --> 00:20:25,708
You’ve already planned it, right?

254
00:20:25,844 --> 00:20:29,731
Come on. Are you planning to introduce him to your mom too?

255
00:20:30,860 --> 00:20:33,613
He must be trying outfits from day one to the last day.

256
00:20:34,217 --> 00:20:37,260
- The sweets are really good. Try them.
- Hey, are you changing the subject?

257
00:20:49,282 --> 00:20:50,408
Which one should I get?

258
00:20:53,751 --> 00:20:55,362
What do you think, P'Fah?

259
00:20:59,109 --> 00:21:00,440
Both of them.

260
00:21:03,477 --> 00:21:05,102
One is enough.

261
00:21:06,234 --> 00:21:08,829
Why? I’ll buy it for you.

262
00:21:10,048 --> 00:21:10,454
Hm?

263
00:21:13,509 --> 00:21:16,096
Then, is there any other one you want to see, Phoon?

264
00:21:16,540 --> 00:21:17,432
Um…

265
00:21:18,814 --> 00:21:19,620
No.

266
00:21:32,491 --> 00:21:33,571
Should I buy a new camera?

267
00:21:35,828 --> 00:21:36,657
Sure.

268
00:21:40,001 --> 00:21:41,284
P'Fah, you should stop me sometimes.

269
00:21:41,823 --> 00:21:42,835
You spoil me completely.

270
00:21:43,005 --> 00:21:46,128
I like seeing you happy.

271
00:21:49,908 --> 00:21:52,976
Now I understand Jo and Hill.

272
00:21:53,592 --> 00:21:57,478
When you have a boyfriend, you just want to indulge him.

273
00:22:02,269 --> 00:22:03,219
You’re not buying it?

274
00:22:06,368 --> 00:22:07,800
Thinking about it…

275
00:22:07,964 --> 00:22:09,322
I already have a lot of cameras.

276
00:22:10,521 --> 00:22:12,690
I’d rather save the money to visit my mom in Japan.

277
00:23:02,517 --> 00:23:04,333
Are you excited about seeing your mom?

278
00:23:05,699 --> 00:23:06,542
I am.

279
00:23:07,145 --> 00:23:08,949
I never thought I’d really get to see her.

280
00:23:10,088 --> 00:23:13,912
At first, I thought she didn’t want to see me anymore.

281
00:23:15,497 --> 00:23:16,838
Why would you think that?

282
00:23:19,200 --> 00:23:20,509
I don’t know.

283
00:23:21,594 --> 00:23:24,517
Maybe I’m just not used to being happy.

284
00:23:30,157 --> 00:23:31,570
Don’t think like that.

285
00:23:33,164 --> 00:23:37,241
You deserve happiness more than anyone. You know that, right?

286
00:23:40,201 --> 00:23:41,493
Thank you.

287
00:24:12,389 --> 00:24:13,293
Are you excited?

288
00:24:15,340 --> 00:24:15,837
Yes.

289
00:24:17,139 --> 00:24:18,435
Very excited.

290
00:24:25,385 --> 00:24:27,063
Do you think it’ll be okay?

291
00:24:28,482 --> 00:24:29,688
It’ll definitely be okay.

292
00:24:30,657 --> 00:24:31,674
Trust me.

293
00:24:49,497 --> 00:24:50,125
Ren.

294
00:24:56,540 --> 00:24:57,668
Mom.

295
00:25:06,625 --> 00:25:08,764
You’ve grown so much.

296
00:25:15,167 --> 00:25:16,552
I came to see you.

297
00:25:23,257 --> 00:25:24,915
Let’s go inside first.

298
00:25:42,352 --> 00:25:44,727
Your name is Tonfah, right?

299
00:25:45,739 --> 00:25:46,825
Yes.

300
00:25:47,121 --> 00:25:49,937
The one who called me.

301
00:25:52,696 --> 00:25:53,634
Yes.

302
00:25:54,091 --> 00:25:54,831
Well…

303
00:25:55,663 --> 00:25:57,251
Phoon really wanted to see you.

304
00:25:58,137 --> 00:25:59,731
So I helped look for you until I found you.

305
00:26:02,034 --> 00:26:07,201
Thank you for bringing my son to see me.

306
00:26:29,845 --> 00:26:30,628
I'm...

307
00:26:32,010 --> 00:26:33,682
I’m really sorry.

308
00:26:36,044 --> 00:26:38,645
Mama loves you.

309
00:26:40,260 --> 00:26:43,297
Mama missed you so much.

310
00:26:44,420 --> 00:26:48,054
I missed you too.

311
00:26:49,925 --> 00:26:51,075
I’ve always wanted to see you.

312
00:27:25,909 --> 00:27:28,007
Hello. Nice to meet you.

313
00:27:28,373 --> 00:27:29,662
I’m P'Tonfah.

314
00:27:30,160 --> 00:27:31,779
Hello. Nice to meet you.

315
00:27:31,967 --> 00:27:33,045
I’m Daiki.

316
00:27:35,168 --> 00:27:36,060
Daiki.

317
00:27:37,808 --> 00:27:39,968
- Tonfah.
- You're so cute.

318
00:27:40,438 --> 00:27:41,081
Thank you.

319
00:27:42,337 --> 00:27:50,675
The first time I went to Phuket was to bring my mother’s ashes back to her hometown.

320
00:27:51,253 --> 00:27:54,054
That’s when I met him.

321
00:27:56,401 --> 00:27:58,314
So my grand-mother was from Phuket.

322
00:27:59,367 --> 00:28:00,407
He…

323
00:28:01,260 --> 00:28:02,463
told me

324
00:28:03,482 --> 00:28:04,908
that he had no family.

325
00:28:06,813 --> 00:28:08,115
And I believed him.

326
00:28:10,654 --> 00:28:11,811
Until I got pregnant.

327
00:28:17,280 --> 00:28:18,136
It’s okay.

328
00:28:18,699 --> 00:28:19,477
Please go on.

329
00:28:19,974 --> 00:28:22,653
He told me to get an abortion.

330
00:28:23,330 --> 00:28:25,991
But I couldn’t do it.

331
00:28:26,348 --> 00:28:30,391
I wanted to raise my child as best as I could.

332
00:28:31,182 --> 00:28:33,728
But it wasn’t easy.

333
00:28:35,161 --> 00:28:37,013
I couldn’t bear seeing you starve.

334
00:28:37,404 --> 00:28:40,527
So I took you to ask him for help.

335
00:28:41,943 --> 00:28:44,560
His wife was furious.

336
00:28:44,795 --> 00:28:46,631
But she felt sorry for you.

337
00:28:47,059 --> 00:28:49,025
So she agreed to raise you.

338
00:28:49,468 --> 00:28:54,121
On the condition that I never interfered with their family again.

339
00:29:04,364 --> 00:29:08,315
She must have been hurt just as much.

340
00:29:10,912 --> 00:29:15,877
We were both hurt by the same man.

341
00:29:23,139 --> 00:29:24,454
I thought

342
00:29:25,016 --> 00:29:31,697
it was better for you. I secretly came to see you many times, but I never dared to approach.

343
00:29:31,920 --> 00:29:34,924
All I could do was send gifts.

344
00:29:35,924 --> 00:29:38,690
I’m sorry. This is my fault.

345
00:29:41,259 --> 00:29:44,780
I’m not here to decide who’s right or wrong.

346
00:29:46,256 --> 00:29:47,484
I don’t resent anyone.

347
00:29:48,232 --> 00:29:49,299
I don’t blame anyone.

348
00:29:50,407 --> 00:29:51,540
That’s all in the past.

349
00:29:53,284 --> 00:29:57,394
Please don’t feel guilty anymore.

350
00:29:59,857 --> 00:30:01,004
At first,

351
00:30:01,614 --> 00:30:04,281
Mama named you Ren.

352
00:30:04,720 --> 00:30:07,557
But they changed your name, didn’t they?

353
00:30:11,672 --> 00:30:14,170
Why did you name me Ren?

354
00:30:14,712 --> 00:30:15,669
Ren

355
00:30:16,013 --> 00:30:18,244
means a lotus.

356
00:30:20,222 --> 00:30:25,797
A lotus that is already beautiful when it’s in the right place.

357
00:30:38,989 --> 00:30:39,767
Daiki.

358
00:30:43,322 --> 00:30:44,733
Go say hello to your big brother.

359
00:30:46,155 --> 00:30:48,028
Hello. Nice to meet you.

360
00:30:50,823 --> 00:30:52,065
He said 'My name is Daiki.

361
00:30:52,444 --> 00:30:53,401
Nice to meet you.'

362
00:30:55,677 --> 00:30:58,186
He’s wanted an older brother for a long time.

363
00:30:59,314 --> 00:31:02,478
He said he’s wanted an older brother for a long time.

364
00:31:03,131 --> 00:31:04,060
Really?

365
00:31:04,528 --> 00:31:07,285
I’ve always wanted a younger brother too.

366
00:31:07,862 --> 00:31:11,068
He said he’s wanted a younger brother too.

367
00:31:13,499 --> 00:31:14,398
Hello.

368
00:31:15,080 --> 00:31:15,623
Hello.

369
00:31:36,053 --> 00:31:37,610
Thank you for letting me come see you.

370
00:31:39,002 --> 00:31:44,125
Why are you talking like we won’t see each other again?

371
00:31:45,063 --> 00:31:46,807
I just wanted you to see

372
00:31:47,394 --> 00:31:48,828
that I’m doing well.

373
00:31:50,450 --> 00:31:51,640
This time,

374
00:31:52,663 --> 00:31:53,884
I just wanted to see

375
00:31:54,334 --> 00:31:55,894
that you’re doing well too.

376
00:32:02,085 --> 00:32:03,379
I want you to be happy

377
00:32:03,740 --> 00:32:04,976
with the path you chose.

378
00:32:06,368 --> 00:32:07,528
As for me,

379
00:32:08,044 --> 00:32:10,351
I’ll be happy with the path I chose too.

380
00:32:12,555 --> 00:32:14,080
Even if we don’t live together,

381
00:32:15,887 --> 00:32:17,530
we still have each other, right?

382
00:32:20,525 --> 00:32:21,312
Mama.

383
00:32:22,192 --> 00:32:24,248
I can still be your mama, right?

384
00:32:30,026 --> 00:32:31,648
No matter what,

385
00:32:33,213 --> 00:32:34,862
I still want you to be my mama.

386
00:32:37,518 --> 00:32:38,296
And I

387
00:32:40,312 --> 00:32:41,380
will always be your Ren.

388
00:32:43,998 --> 00:32:47,354
We’ll get to see each other again, right?

389
00:32:50,448 --> 00:32:52,280
Come visit often, okay?

390
00:32:58,928 --> 00:33:00,525
I’ll come back to visit often.

391
00:33:02,626 --> 00:33:04,909
He said he’ll come back to visit again.

392
00:33:09,174 --> 00:33:10,259
Goodbye.

393
00:33:11,017 --> 00:33:11,653
Goodbye.

394
00:33:14,468 --> 00:33:18,201
Please take care of your health.

395
00:33:19,183 --> 00:33:19,977
I will.

396
00:33:22,743 --> 00:33:23,731
Goodbye.

397
00:33:31,940 --> 00:33:32,740
Thank you.

398
00:33:33,299 --> 00:33:36,202
Please take good care of Ren.

399
00:33:38,034 --> 00:33:45,154
I’ll take care of and protect your son with my life.

400
00:33:47,585 --> 00:33:48,543
Thank you.

401
00:33:48,570 --> 00:33:49,299
Thank you.

402
00:34:08,561 --> 00:34:09,724
You're really kind.

403
00:34:13,231 --> 00:34:14,242
Yes, you are.

404
00:34:14,425 --> 00:34:15,988
You're incredibly kind.

405
00:34:16,730 --> 00:34:20,448
Not many people would be happy when their parents remarry.

406
00:34:21,068 --> 00:34:23,385
And on top of that, you love you half-brother like this.

407
00:34:26,389 --> 00:34:27,678
Well, Daiki is adorable.

408
00:34:35,133 --> 00:34:39,069
I think you and your mom are really alike.

409
00:34:39,829 --> 00:34:40,783
How so?

410
00:34:43,441 --> 00:34:45,343
Probably you guys faces look similar.

411
00:34:46,232 --> 00:34:47,620
Especially the eyes.

412
00:34:53,768 --> 00:34:59,951
Thank you for giving him such a beautiful and radiant smile.

413
00:35:00,555 --> 00:35:06,773
He’s beautiful and radiant on his own.

414
00:35:08,817 --> 00:35:18,360
Because of the path you chose twenty years ago, I’ve had him to love until today.

415
00:35:19,146 --> 00:35:22,010
Thank you so much.

416
00:35:45,482 --> 00:35:46,342
How's going?

417
00:35:47,284 --> 00:35:48,008
How are things?

418
00:35:48,648 --> 00:35:49,471
Well…

419
00:35:49,856 --> 00:35:50,617
It’s cold.

420
00:35:52,626 --> 00:35:54,228
Where’s P'Fah?

421
00:35:54,847 --> 00:35:56,525
He looked tired, so he fell asleep.

422
00:35:57,075 --> 00:35:59,022
So I came out for a walk in the garden.

423
00:36:01,540 --> 00:36:02,927
Morning, little one.

424
00:36:03,041 --> 00:36:04,386
Why did you get out of bed?

425
00:36:07,133 --> 00:36:07,760
Uh…

426
00:36:09,405 --> 00:36:10,173
Whoa.

427
00:36:14,601 --> 00:36:15,694
Why are you calling?

428
00:36:17,718 --> 00:36:18,880
He wanted to talk to Phoon.

429
00:36:19,456 --> 00:36:20,168
Oh?

430
00:36:21,056 --> 00:36:21,795
I’ll hang up now.

431
00:36:35,290 --> 00:36:37,105
Are you okay, Phoon?

432
00:36:38,277 --> 00:36:40,077
P'Fah, it’s just that…

433
00:36:40,712 --> 00:36:41,620
Earlier…

434
00:36:43,037 --> 00:36:43,958
What is it?

435
00:36:44,325 --> 00:36:46,140
Everyone saw it already.

436
00:36:46,731 --> 00:36:48,029
The morning kiss?

437
00:36:48,896 --> 00:36:49,878
It’s okay.

438
00:36:50,204 --> 00:36:51,425
Don’t overthink it, Phoon.

439
00:36:51,909 --> 00:36:53,534
How can it be okay?

440
00:36:58,151 --> 00:36:59,014
Are you upset?

441
00:36:59,389 --> 00:36:59,986
Yes.

442
00:37:00,949 --> 00:37:02,321
Very upset.

443
00:37:08,610 --> 00:37:10,921
- What are you doing?
- Making it up to you.

444
00:37:11,648 --> 00:37:13,302
Who makes up like this?

445
00:37:13,712 --> 00:37:14,841
I do.

446
00:37:15,343 --> 00:37:17,094
Who told you to get out of bed?

447
00:37:17,312 --> 00:37:18,534
You looked tired.

448
00:37:18,962 --> 00:37:21,499
So I didn’t want to disturb you.

449
00:37:25,244 --> 00:37:25,672
Okay.

450
00:37:28,850 --> 00:37:29,306
Okay?

451
00:37:30,902 --> 00:37:33,451
I understand now.

452
00:37:33,894 --> 00:37:35,663
But you can’t tease mr like that.

453
00:37:37,281 --> 00:37:39,122
I wasn’t teasing you.

454
00:37:39,712 --> 00:37:41,474
I really didn’t see it.

455
00:37:42,977 --> 00:37:44,807
- Really?
- Really.

456
00:37:45,155 --> 00:37:47,117
I never tease you.

457
00:37:47,645 --> 00:37:49,425
You tease me the most.

458
00:37:50,048 --> 00:37:50,838
Hey.

459
00:37:51,530 --> 00:37:52,365
Then…

460
00:37:52,905 --> 00:37:54,534
Let’s not count what just happened.

461
00:37:54,801 --> 00:37:57,737
I think we need a proper round.

462
00:37:59,754 --> 00:38:01,019
A proper round?

463
00:38:01,856 --> 00:38:02,558
Well…

464
00:38:02,949 --> 00:38:04,605
A real morning kiss.

465
00:38:05,457 --> 00:38:06,508
That’s not it.

466
00:38:06,925 --> 00:38:07,942
Right?

467
00:38:08,202 --> 00:38:09,568
Just one morning kiss.

468
00:38:23,075 --> 00:38:24,525
Good morning again.

469
00:38:26,188 --> 00:38:28,248
Good morning.

470
00:39:06,835 --> 00:39:08,721
I heard from Ter that today’s Phoon's birthday?

471
00:39:09,426 --> 00:39:09,997
Yeah.

472
00:39:11,228 --> 00:39:12,434
I sent my gift with Ter.

473
00:39:13,014 --> 00:39:13,954
Thanks, man.

474
00:39:14,367 --> 00:39:16,520
Every birthday gives me a headache.

475
00:39:16,657 --> 00:39:18,093
I never know what to buy.

476
00:39:18,254 --> 00:39:19,469
I let North choose, I’ll pay for it.

477
00:39:21,180 --> 00:39:22,645
That’s so you, Jo.

478
00:39:23,392 --> 00:39:24,577
Hey, buy one for me too.

479
00:39:24,922 --> 00:39:27,762
- Go ask your Papa.
- Hey, watch your mouth.

480
00:39:28,644 --> 00:39:30,825
Hi, Papa.

481
00:39:32,740 --> 00:39:33,906
So what did you buy for him?

482
00:40:02,069 --> 00:40:04,666
Happy Birthday, my little one.

483
00:40:04,896 --> 00:40:07,788
May every day from now on be a good day for you.

484
00:40:08,324 --> 00:40:11,404
May all your wishes come true.

485
00:40:11,854 --> 00:40:14,182
P'Fah will always be cheering you on.

486
00:40:41,798 --> 00:40:42,813
Thank you.

487
00:40:47,533 --> 00:40:48,367
A camera?

488
00:40:49,074 --> 00:40:49,628
How much?

489
00:40:50,668 --> 00:40:51,568
Just over a hundred thousand.

490
00:40:52,340 --> 00:40:52,949
What?!

491
00:40:54,536 --> 00:40:56,210
So you’re one of those people too now?

492
00:40:56,231 --> 00:41:00,090
Fah, once you have a boyfriend, you love like crazy, huh?

493
00:41:00,194 --> 00:41:01,882
- You don’t have one.
- Hey.

494
00:41:01,933 --> 00:41:04,536
- Watch your mouth.
- Better that way.

495
00:41:04,841 --> 00:41:06,471
- I pity for his boyfriend.
- Wow.

496
00:41:07,259 --> 00:41:09,887
You guys are such jerks.

497
00:41:11,665 --> 00:41:13,080
Is Arthit sulking?

498
00:41:15,998 --> 00:41:19,011
Wow, P'Fah bought a camera as a gift?

499
00:41:19,272 --> 00:41:20,291
Yeah.

500
00:41:20,362 --> 00:41:24,345
That’s huge. My gift and Jo’s look so little now.

501
00:41:26,817 --> 00:41:27,640
What gift of yours?

502
00:41:28,435 --> 00:41:29,077
Here.

503
00:41:29,520 --> 00:41:31,705
- From me and P'Hill.
- Thank you.

504
00:41:31,736 --> 00:41:32,908
You’re definitely going to like it.

505
00:41:33,931 --> 00:41:36,454
Just the fact that you guys remembered my birthday already makes me happy.

506
00:41:38,269 --> 00:41:40,285
If you’re really happy, then I’ll take it back.

507
00:41:40,311 --> 00:41:41,522
- No.
- What?

508
00:41:41,856 --> 00:41:42,558
Hey!

509
00:41:42,914 --> 00:41:43,920
You’re pulling so hard.

510
00:41:44,499 --> 00:41:45,882
Why did you have to be born today?

511
00:41:46,915 --> 00:41:48,122
I want to go celebrate too.

512
00:41:48,835 --> 00:41:51,194
Then cancel your family plans and come celebrate my birthday with me.

513
00:41:51,600 --> 00:41:54,241
Oh, so if I get cut out of the inheritance,

514
00:41:54,450 --> 00:41:55,468
are you going to take care of me?

515
00:41:56,020 --> 00:41:57,662
Nope.

516
00:41:58,965 --> 00:41:59,957
Ugh.

517
00:42:00,586 --> 00:42:02,656
Let’s check out the birthday gifts and see what I got.

518
00:42:02,983 --> 00:42:03,751
Whose should we open first?

519
00:42:06,469 --> 00:42:09,785
Save mine for last. Start with the gloomy-looking box first—it looks nicely depressing.

520
00:42:09,814 --> 00:42:11,697
- That’s bullying.
- It’s cool.

521
00:42:11,724 --> 00:42:14,477
Bullying. You’re exaggerating.

522
00:42:14,511 --> 00:42:16,185
It’s style, just look at it.

523
00:42:16,254 --> 00:42:17,808
Simple but classy.

524
00:42:18,013 --> 00:42:20,029
Or start from Dao's?

525
00:42:20,746 --> 00:42:21,891
Did you get me an amulet or what?

526
00:42:34,685 --> 00:42:35,720
Taking photos again?

527
00:42:37,208 --> 00:42:38,198
P'Fah, look.

528
00:42:39,322 --> 00:42:40,518
You look like a model.

529
00:42:43,222 --> 00:42:44,700
That’s because the photographer is good.

530
00:42:53,202 --> 00:42:54,685
Time really flies, doesn’t it?

531
00:42:56,413 --> 00:42:58,684
It feels like we were just here not long ago.

532
00:43:00,620 --> 00:43:01,413
Yeah.

533
00:43:05,589 --> 00:43:06,650
Do you remember, P'Fah?

534
00:43:07,057 --> 00:43:08,392
You said that…

535
00:43:08,921 --> 00:43:12,069
"I can’t be the sky for anyone."

536
00:43:15,143 --> 00:43:16,081
I remember.

537
00:43:16,728 --> 00:43:18,188
Do you still feel that way now?

538
00:43:24,244 --> 00:43:25,490
If that’s what Phoon wants,

539
00:43:25,826 --> 00:43:27,278
I can be anything for you.

540
00:43:31,665 --> 00:43:32,865
Thank you for bringing me here.

541
00:43:34,690 --> 00:43:35,805
Thank you again.

542
00:43:36,847 --> 00:43:38,077
Thank you so much.

543
00:43:39,315 --> 00:43:41,385
Even though you have been so busy,

544
00:43:42,441 --> 00:43:44,217
you still made time to be with me on my birthday.

545
00:43:48,117 --> 00:43:49,952
I don’t really do much for you, P'Fah.

546
00:43:52,454 --> 00:43:53,940
Just being a good kid is enough, Phoon.

547
00:43:55,115 --> 00:43:56,223
I'm a good kid.

548
00:43:56,518 --> 00:43:59,352
- And not naughty.
- You are. A naughty cat.

549
00:43:59,542 --> 00:44:01,340
I’m not naughty. And I’m not a cat either.

550
00:44:02,225 --> 00:44:03,208
Why not?

551
00:44:03,548 --> 00:44:05,400
Even your friends call you maew.

552
00:44:12,007 --> 00:44:13,383
- Maew.
- Yes?

553
00:44:15,622 --> 00:44:17,887
See? You said you weren’t a cat.

554
00:44:18,253 --> 00:44:19,314
Then why did you answer?

555
00:44:22,628 --> 00:44:24,564
If I were a cat,

556
00:44:25,512 --> 00:44:28,127
and really had nine lives,

557
00:44:29,767 --> 00:44:30,857
I’d give them all to you, P'Fah.

558
00:44:31,075 --> 00:44:32,851
Hmm? All of them?

559
00:44:34,152 --> 00:44:35,121
All of them.

560
00:44:39,714 --> 00:44:40,882
I’ll put them right into your hands.

561
00:44:42,902 --> 00:44:43,848
Okay.

562
00:44:44,367 --> 00:44:46,207
Then I’ll gladly take them all.

563
00:44:53,794 --> 00:44:55,062
Happy birthday.

564
00:44:56,524 --> 00:44:59,430
Thank you for becoming the best thing in my life.

565
00:45:31,173 --> 00:45:33,191
Come on, cheers!

566
00:45:33,725 --> 00:45:34,797
Yeah.

567
00:45:37,703 --> 00:45:39,011
Thanks for coming, Dao.

568
00:45:40,017 --> 00:45:42,425
It’s Maew’s birthday—how could I not come?

569
00:45:43,567 --> 00:45:47,063
Yeah, if you don’t come to my birthday, we’ll see about that.

570
00:45:49,714 --> 00:45:50,816
You get sulky so easily.

571
00:46:04,208 --> 00:46:05,979
It’s empty—time for a refill.

572
00:46:06,997 --> 00:46:08,020
Straight up.

573
00:46:08,648 --> 00:46:09,720
Hey, Jo.

574
00:46:09,965 --> 00:46:11,149
Control your boyfriend.

575
00:46:11,220 --> 00:46:12,429
Hey, he’s having fun.

576
00:46:13,109 --> 00:46:14,949
- Right?
- I am.

577
00:46:18,974 --> 00:46:20,220
- North.
- What?

578
00:46:20,271 --> 00:46:21,380
Are you trying to get me drunk?

579
00:46:22,059 --> 00:46:23,552
No way.

580
00:46:24,222 --> 00:46:26,222
How are you this strong with alcohol?

581
00:46:26,586 --> 00:46:27,561
That’s impossible.

582
00:46:27,749 --> 00:46:29,597
Let’s settle this.

583
00:46:30,511 --> 00:46:31,482
Whoever gets drunk wins—

584
00:46:31,800 --> 00:46:33,437
no, whoever gets drunk first loses.

585
00:46:33,450 --> 00:46:34,628
- Deal.
- Yeah.

586
00:46:35,296 --> 00:46:35,995
Let’s go.

587
00:46:36,149 --> 00:46:37,777
- Bring it on.
- Yeah, bring it.

588
00:46:37,816 --> 00:46:39,746
- Come on.
- Let’s go.

589
00:46:39,918 --> 00:46:43,854
Cheers. Bottoms up.

590
00:46:49,091 --> 00:46:50,967
I love P'Hill the most.

591
00:46:53,260 --> 00:46:57,222
Throwing up doesn’t count—but if you pass out, you lose.

592
00:46:58,872 --> 00:46:59,903
Cheers.

593
00:47:08,650 --> 00:47:11,826
Yes! I won!

594
00:47:14,866 --> 00:47:15,761
Yes, little one.

595
00:47:16,460 --> 00:47:17,315
You won.

596
00:47:20,770 --> 00:47:21,496
Ugh.

597
00:47:22,090 --> 00:47:24,182
Why was I even born a refrigerator?

598
00:47:24,389 --> 00:47:26,271
If I can’t even chill chicken in it.

599
00:47:27,256 --> 00:47:28,434
So annoying.

600
00:47:41,931 --> 00:47:44,160
I’ll go get a towel to wipe you down, okay?

601
00:47:46,920 --> 00:47:47,554
No.

602
00:47:50,561 --> 00:47:53,374
- I’ll just go grab a towel for a second, Phoon.
- No.

603
00:47:54,395 --> 00:47:57,644
No matter how good a person you meet,

604
00:47:58,429 --> 00:48:00,189
don’t ever leave me behind, okay?

605
00:48:04,143 --> 00:48:05,595
What are you talking about, Phoon?

606
00:48:05,979 --> 00:48:07,379
I don’t know. I’m drunk.

607
00:48:22,139 --> 00:48:22,958
P’Mhor.

608
00:48:23,379 --> 00:48:24,502
P’Mhor Fah.

609
00:48:24,608 --> 00:48:25,204
Yes?

610
00:48:27,299 --> 00:48:28,450
Don’t let me find out, okay?

611
00:48:30,275 --> 00:48:31,192
Find out about what?

612
00:48:31,800 --> 00:48:36,607
That you were secretly checking someone else out during class.

613
00:48:38,521 --> 00:48:39,272
Really?

614
00:48:44,379 --> 00:48:45,505
P’Fah, do you like kids?

615
00:48:46,789 --> 00:48:47,792
Kids?

616
00:48:49,742 --> 00:48:51,722
Yeah, I do.

617
00:48:52,404 --> 00:48:53,103
Why?

618
00:48:54,728 --> 00:48:56,758
I like kids too.

619
00:48:57,244 --> 00:48:58,970
I want to have children.

620
00:48:59,620 --> 00:49:00,654
A whole house full of them.

621
00:49:01,780 --> 00:49:07,211
But P’Fah probably won’t have time for the kids.

622
00:49:07,752 --> 00:49:09,829
They’d love me more than you anyway.

623
00:49:12,180 --> 00:49:15,183
I would be Papa.

624
00:49:15,662 --> 00:49:17,435
The Papa who understands the kids the most.

625
00:49:25,151 --> 00:49:26,888
Why aren’t you answering, P’Fah?

626
00:49:28,179 --> 00:49:28,911
Well…

627
00:49:29,438 --> 00:49:31,074
You didn’t really ask me anything, Phoon.

628
00:49:33,416 --> 00:49:36,309
Then what would P’Fah name our child?

629
00:49:37,592 --> 00:49:38,814
A name?

630
00:49:42,934 --> 00:49:44,361
What should it be?

631
00:49:46,445 --> 00:49:48,611
I don’t know. You can decide, Phoon.

632
00:49:49,902 --> 00:49:51,712
But P’Fah works really hard.

633
00:49:52,668 --> 00:49:56,835
Will P’Fah even have time for me and the kids?

634
00:49:59,822 --> 00:50:04,148
Don’t worry, Phoon. I’ll try my best to make time for you and the kids.

635
00:50:04,434 --> 00:50:08,562
Then P’Fah has to be a really sweet Papa to them.

636
00:50:09,337 --> 00:50:10,211
I will.

637
00:50:10,592 --> 00:50:11,645
But right now,

638
00:50:12,693 --> 00:50:13,797
it’s already late.

639
00:50:14,242 --> 00:50:15,161
Let’s go to sleep, okay?

640
00:50:15,367 --> 00:50:17,798
No. I won’t sleep. I’m not sleepy.

641
00:50:17,884 --> 00:50:19,870
- But you’re drunk, Phoon.
- I’m not.

642
00:50:20,551 --> 00:50:22,263
Why is Papa arguing with me?

643
00:50:22,976 --> 00:50:23,714
Wait a second…

644
00:50:24,354 --> 00:50:25,616
"Papa"?

645
00:50:25,909 --> 00:50:27,505
Papa’s arguing with me.

646
00:50:28,725 --> 00:50:31,160
Phoon, don’t be naughty.

647
00:50:33,114 --> 00:50:36,557
Papa scolds me—do you scold the kids too?

648
00:50:37,820 --> 00:50:39,616
If they’re naughty, then I have to.

649
00:50:39,660 --> 00:50:41,050
No, don’t scold them.

650
00:50:41,457 --> 00:50:44,480
If Papa scolds the kids, I’ll take them and run away.

651
00:50:44,768 --> 00:50:46,019
I won’t let them see you.

652
00:50:51,460 --> 00:50:52,361
In that case…

653
00:50:53,524 --> 00:50:55,245
Mama, don’t be so mean to Papa, okay?

654
00:51:01,952 --> 00:51:04,285
Ow, it hurts here.

655
00:51:04,548 --> 00:51:05,767
It hurts here.

656
00:51:19,570 --> 00:51:21,220
It hurts here too.

657
00:51:33,937 --> 00:51:34,681
Good night.

658
00:51:47,709 --> 00:51:48,471
Here you go, Phoon.

659
00:51:49,005 --> 00:51:49,804
Careful, it’s hot.

660
00:52:03,293 --> 00:52:04,253
Do you have a headache?

661
00:52:06,321 --> 00:52:08,517
A little.

662
00:52:08,709 --> 00:52:09,666
Next time,

663
00:52:10,038 --> 00:52:11,677
don’t drink this much, okay?

664
00:52:15,848 --> 00:52:16,324
Mm.

665
00:52:17,426 --> 00:52:19,480
It’s good. Did you make this yourself, P’Fah?

666
00:52:19,912 --> 00:52:20,708
I did.

667
00:52:21,309 --> 00:52:22,213
If you like it,

668
00:52:22,408 --> 00:52:23,263
eat a lot, okay?

669
00:52:31,674 --> 00:52:32,456
Phoon.

670
00:52:33,931 --> 00:52:35,422
Do you remember what you said

671
00:52:35,816 --> 00:52:37,062
last night?

672
00:52:38,124 --> 00:52:39,245
Last night?

673
00:52:40,088 --> 00:52:41,062
Why?

674
00:52:42,302 --> 00:52:44,478
You talked about

675
00:52:45,394 --> 00:52:46,282
having kids.

676
00:52:50,637 --> 00:52:51,631
Kids?

677
00:52:51,893 --> 00:52:52,570
Yes.

678
00:52:53,543 --> 00:52:56,837
You asked, “Does P’Fah like kids?”

679
00:52:56,942 --> 00:52:58,896
"Does P’Fah want to have kids?"

680
00:53:02,078 --> 00:53:06,268
Oh… I must’ve been drunk last night.

681
00:53:06,537 --> 00:53:07,508
I was just rambling.

682
00:53:16,423 --> 00:53:18,226
I won’t drink anymore.

683
00:53:19,521 --> 00:53:20,600
Why not?

684
00:53:22,386 --> 00:53:26,122
I think you’re pretty cute when you’re drunk.

685
00:53:29,533 --> 00:53:33,182
But you just told me not to drink too much.

686
00:53:35,764 --> 00:53:36,737
That’s true.

687
00:53:38,010 --> 00:53:42,293
I mean, you can drink—but only when I’m with you.

688
00:53:51,355 --> 00:53:52,608
Eat a lot, okay?

689
00:53:53,162 --> 00:53:54,327
- Mama.
- Hmm?

690
00:53:58,217 --> 00:54:02,041
If you’re still hungry, Papa can make more for you.

691
00:54:07,613 --> 00:54:08,739
Daotok.

692
00:54:10,157 --> 00:54:15,162
If you keep staring at us like that, I’m gonna puke on you.

693
00:54:17,277 --> 00:54:18,440
Don’t talk about puking.

694
00:54:18,887 --> 00:54:22,834
Enough. Stop arguing and help me check the exam results.

695
00:54:22,986 --> 00:54:24,497
Come help me root for this.

696
00:54:26,300 --> 00:54:27,182
Get up.

697
00:54:31,840 --> 00:54:34,025
Exam Results Announcement
Faculty of Fine Arts, Bachelor of Fine Arts Program, Creative Photography
Teerapat Chaowakornkul

698
00:54:36,174 --> 00:54:36,906
Shit.

699
00:54:43,823 --> 00:54:44,937
It’s okay, man.

700
00:54:46,568 --> 00:54:48,540
If I don’t get in this year, I can try again next year.

701
00:54:51,285 --> 00:54:53,146
You got in—holy shit, you got in!

702
00:54:53,191 --> 00:54:56,137
Your name’s on it. Come take a look.

703
00:54:56,949 --> 00:54:58,960
Thirasophon University announces the admission results for Program Choice No. 6
Teerapat Chaowakornkul

704
00:55:00,468 --> 00:55:01,875
- I got in!
- Yeah.

705
00:55:02,133 --> 00:55:04,957
Yes!

706
00:55:55,525 --> 00:55:59,952
The sky is never the same each day, but it’s still just as captivating.

707
00:56:23,066 --> 00:56:26,001
To Typhoon,

708
00:56:31,293 --> 00:56:34,832
Even though I’ve written countless letters,

709
00:56:37,168 --> 00:56:39,810
to so many people,

710
00:56:42,157 --> 00:56:46,011
this is probably the first time I’ve ever written one to myself.

711
00:57:28,428 --> 00:57:29,454
Thank you.

712
00:57:45,589 --> 00:57:47,600
Thank you for growing stronger,

713
00:57:50,007 --> 00:57:52,297
and for accepting your own pain.

714
00:57:59,934 --> 00:58:02,149
Thank you for finding yourself in the end.

715
00:58:03,622 --> 00:58:08,358
Thank you for daring to open your heart, and for meeting so many good people along the way.

716
00:58:08,474 --> 00:58:09,503
Hey, you.

717
00:58:09,786 --> 00:58:10,877
The classroom’s this way.

718
00:58:12,801 --> 00:58:13,946
Yeah, I’m in the faculty.

719
00:58:14,493 --> 00:58:17,274
What should we do? That Phoon still gets lost like always.

720
00:58:17,848 --> 00:58:19,345
Will he survive without us?

721
00:58:23,213 --> 00:58:26,591
Are classes over yet? I’ll come pick you up.

722
00:58:29,939 --> 00:58:31,222
No need.

723
00:58:32,831 --> 00:58:33,945
Why not?

724
00:58:37,770 --> 00:58:43,788
Thank you for believing in love, enough to realize just how deeply you’re capable of loving someone.

725
00:58:50,100 --> 00:58:52,312
- Where to next?
- Maybe go eat.

726
00:58:52,797 --> 00:58:53,280
What about you?

727
00:58:53,760 --> 00:58:54,499
No idea.

728
00:58:55,232 --> 00:58:55,979
I’m hungry too.

729
00:58:56,961 --> 00:58:57,893
But I don’t feel like eating with you.

730
00:58:58,509 --> 00:58:59,472
What’s wrong with you?

731
00:59:00,848 --> 00:59:02,010
Phoon won’t let me go pick him up.

732
00:59:06,280 --> 00:59:09,946
Or maybe he’s studying photography now and totally surrounded by people.

733
00:59:09,964 --> 00:59:11,361
- Yeah, probably.
- Like Hill said.

734
00:59:15,192 --> 00:59:18,367
Oh, poor you, P'Fah.

735
00:59:18,962 --> 00:59:20,571
Your life is so tragic.

736
00:59:21,288 --> 00:59:24,560
Don’t listen to those idiots too much.
You know Phoon loves you to death.

737
00:59:24,717 --> 00:59:25,321
I know.

738
00:59:25,737 --> 00:59:27,162
I don’t believe a word those two say anyway.

739
00:59:27,296 --> 00:59:29,170
Huh?

740
00:59:30,331 --> 00:59:32,382
- Hey, Jo, did you hear that?
- Yeah.

741
00:59:32,500 --> 00:59:34,241
- See you at P'Gib’s shop.
- What the hell?

742
00:59:34,256 --> 00:59:34,986
He’s getting bold these days.

743
00:59:35,777 --> 00:59:36,890
Smiling nonstop.

744
00:59:41,657 --> 00:59:42,562
Where’s Phoon?

745
00:59:45,614 --> 00:59:46,423
Here.

746
01:00:06,444 --> 01:00:10,253
If it’s not too much trouble, may I see you again?

747
01:00:10,946 --> 01:00:13,122
There’s something important I’d like to talk to you about.

748
01:00:14,407 --> 01:00:16,082
- Thank you.
- You’re welcome.

749
01:00:27,016 --> 01:00:28,266
What’s up, little one?

750
01:00:41,555 --> 01:00:42,558
Hello.

751
01:00:46,533 --> 01:00:47,373
Hello.

752
01:00:49,685 --> 01:00:51,462
Thank you for meeting me.

753
01:00:54,441 --> 01:00:56,134
Thank you for coming to see me as well.

754
01:00:59,546 --> 01:01:05,146
Have you ever wondered what you would’ve done if I had walked away back then?

755
01:01:08,805 --> 01:01:13,321
Like I said before, I’d go back to the same place—where we feel at ease.

756
01:01:13,685 --> 01:01:15,075
No matter how long it takes.

757
01:01:23,777 --> 01:01:25,989
No matter how long, you’d still wait?

758
01:01:28,223 --> 01:01:28,980
Yes.

759
01:01:34,997 --> 01:01:35,823
One year.

760
01:01:37,130 --> 01:01:37,783
That’s fine.

761
01:01:42,617 --> 01:01:43,662
Two years.

762
01:01:44,250 --> 01:01:45,032
That’s still fine.

763
01:01:45,580 --> 01:01:46,829
Five years.

764
01:01:47,654 --> 01:01:48,407
That’s fine too.

765
01:01:48,635 --> 01:01:49,730
Then ten years.

766
01:01:50,801 --> 01:01:52,841
Phoon, stop teasing me already.

767
01:01:56,419 --> 01:01:57,826
I’m going to start counting down.

768
01:01:58,432 --> 01:02:01,468
If you still don’t say anything, you’ll be punished.

769
01:02:02,823 --> 01:02:03,656
Ten.

770
01:02:04,311 --> 01:02:05,034
Nine.

771
01:02:05,663 --> 01:02:06,337
Eight.

772
01:02:07,082 --> 01:02:07,681
Seven.

773
01:02:08,565 --> 01:02:09,050
Six.

774
01:02:10,059 --> 01:02:10,909
Five.

775
01:02:11,666 --> 01:02:12,687
- Four.
- P'Fah.

776
01:02:12,733 --> 01:02:14,334
- P'Fah.
- Three.

777
01:02:14,364 --> 01:02:15,365
I just—

778
01:02:15,463 --> 01:02:16,706
- Two.
- wanted to surprise you, that’s all.

779
01:02:17,025 --> 01:02:17,957
One.

780
01:02:18,272 --> 01:02:19,114
P'…

781
01:02:43,505 --> 01:02:44,820
I loves you, P'Fah.

782
01:02:46,882 --> 01:02:48,394
I loves you too, phoon.
